The paper deals with motion planning for robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). It also involves uncertainty and probabilistic collision avoidance, which are common themes in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses statistical techniques such as Monte Carlo sampling, control variates, and importance sampling, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
